{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778247958,"nonce":"3qsfbk9vvVonoOQGKPsD83KD8Yg=","message":"**Final integration of the C\u0026S-faithful Riccati fix + the empirical peak-velocity Δv on trained flavor-B controllers. The picture has shifted substantially from the prior comment `43d6378`.**\n\nBoth threads landed on integration branch `feature/cs-dv-investigation-integration` (final SHA `f976073`); synthesis doc `results/flavor_a_vs_b/synthesis.md` updated in §4.2 / §5.4 / §7.1.1 / §7.2 / §8.0 / §8.0.1.\n\n- **The (a)/(b) framing was misdiagnosed.** C\u0026S's H∞ is essentially what we'd call flavor-(a) (free additive disturbance ε with γ²-cost), with  = I_n$ (full-state, per Eq 13). The previously-xfailed `test_cs_faithful_qr_velocity_inflation` was xfailing because the rlrmp default $ uses the 2D velocity-force channel (matching the curl-field intervenor), not because (a) and (b) differ. With `cs_faithful_pointmass()` (`disturbance_channel=\"full_state\"`) the test now passes: Δv = +1.00% at .5\\gamma_*$ on the C\u0026S regime, +2.35% near the boundary; +1.53% on the rlrmp regime under C\u0026S Q,R. Synthesis §4.2 / §5.4 reframed; §7.2 retained as a valid (if negative) statement about S-procedure $\\Delta A569XlFrobenius robustness, but no longer load-bearing for the C\u0026S replication.\n\n- **Empirical Δv on trained flavor-B controllers is NEGATIVE** at the group mean: −20.75% / −26.40% / −25.68% across η_max ∈ {0.03, 0.10, 0.30}, on 45 replicates (3 η_max × 3 seeds × 5 reps), single canonical reach, no test-time perturbation. Replicate-level distribution is **bimodal** (~20–27% at +40 to +57%, the rest at −12 to −73%). Trained controllers are *slower* than the no-perturbation baseline — opposite sign to the corrected analytical prediction (Δv = +10.8% on the rlrmp regime under flavor-(a) velocity-force $).\n\n- **Joint reading.** Flavor-B training is **not** producing C\u0026S-style robust H∞ controllers. The pre-registered (a) ⊊ (b) thesis is both *reframed* — flavor-(b) is not needed for the C\u0026S Δv signature; flavor-(a) full-state $ alone reaches +Δv analytically — and *complicated* — the empirical training-vs-analytical mismatch is the new central question, not whether the Riccati formulation needs (b). Candidate hypotheses for the mismatch (see synthesis §8.0.1): training-loss-vs-controller-cost mismatch, sub-optimal PGD inner loop, channel mismatch between PGD-Frobenius $\\Delta A$ and analytical free-ε, architecture/regularisation. Highest-priority next step: retrain with controller cost aligned to the H∞ objective (Q ramp, terminal $, matched disturbance channel).\n\nCross-refs: synthesis §7.1.1 / §7.2 / §8.0 (commit `f976073` on integration branch); `97c227a` (analytical fix, SHA `0c160e9`); `c723082` (empirical Δv, SHA `4657029`).","files":null}]}